                                                                                                                                   Minority scholarships

     OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 
               
	New Delhi, Jan. 30: The cabinet committee for economic affairs today approved Rs 25 lakh merit-cum-means scholarships for schoolchildren belonging to minority communities under the 11th five-year plan. 
    
	Officials of the ministry of minority affairs said they planned to launch the scheme in February. 
    
	Students from Classes I to X will be eligible for the scholarships. Thirty per cent of the scholarships will be reserved for girls and can be transferred to boys only if there arent enough girls. 
    
	About Rs 1868.5 crore have been approved for the scheme, of which Rs 1408.4 crore will be contributed by the Centre and the rest by state governments. 
    
	The government will pay a maximum tuition fee of Rs 350 a month for each student. The selected students will receive Rs 100 per month for books, bags and stationery. In addition, students in hostels from Class VI upwards will receive Rs 500.
                                                                                
